data.name: lblEnableOutbound.HelpText
data.value:
If this is checked, the owner of this extension will be permitted to make outbound calls to public telephone numbers.
If this is not checked, the owner of this extension will not be permitted to make outbound calls to public telephone numbers.

data.name: lblEnableOutbound.Text
data.value: Allow outbound calls to other telephones

data.name: lblCallScreen.HelpText
data.value:
If this is checked, CallButler will announce who the caller is and give the extension owner the opportunity to answer the call or have it sent to Voicemail.
If this is not checked, CallButler will automatically connect the caller without an announcement.

data.name: lblHandoff.HelpText
data.value:
If the person at this extension chooses to take a call and this is checked, CallButler will attempt to hand off both calls to the telephone provider. Once the calls are handed off, CallButler will hang up and no longer participate in the conversation.
Checking this can save network bandwidth and CPU resources, but will disable any in-call features.
Note: This feature may not be supported with all Internet telephone providers.

data.name: lblDialByName.HelpText
data.value: Callers may choose to find extensions by entering the first three digits of a person's last name. If you would like this extension to be hidden from callers when they search by name, uncheck this box. Otherwise this extension will be included in the list of search results.

data.name: lblRemoteManagement.HelpText
data.value:
Check this if you want to allow the owner of this extension to be able to manage it over the phone or from their own computer.
To manage this extension from another computer you will need to install the CallButler Message Center client. With the CallButler message center client your users can:
- Listen to their voicemail - Change their voicemail greeting - Change their Find Me numbers.
To manage this extension from a phone you will need to call the main number and enter the extension number for this extension. You may then press the * (star) key at which point you will be prompted for your passcode.

data.name: label6.Text
data.value:
You can allow your employees to manage their own extensions by allowing them to download the CallButler Extension Management Client. The Extension Management Client will allow an extension user to listen to their voicemail, change their voicemail greeting and much more.
To help the user at this extension, CallButler can send an Email with download and setup instructions. Would you like to send setup instructions to the user at this extension?
